WEBVTT

00:02:05.358 --> 00:02:06.459
You forgot something.

00:02:08.795 --> 00:02:11.865
As you can see,
I'm just some old man.

00:02:12.365 --> 00:02:14.300
Unfortunately, I don't have any children.

00:02:14.367 --> 00:02:16.136
I never said it was yours.

00:02:16.202 --> 00:02:19.305
Oh, was it a customer's?
I will hold it, then.

00:02:22.842 --> 00:02:23.710
How about it?

00:02:24.177 --> 00:02:25.278
Wanna go somewhere?

00:02:25.612 --> 00:02:27.514
It's a little too early to go to bed.

00:02:27.847 --> 00:02:30.216
I'm an early riser. I go to sleep early.

00:02:30.683 --> 00:02:34.154
If you want a prim and proper life,
I have just the place for you.

00:02:34.621 --> 00:02:37.590
A hotel where you get three meals
and a bodyguard, all for free.

00:02:37.657 --> 00:02:39.859
I'm sure that's impossible
without a reservation.

00:02:40.493 --> 00:02:42.529
I'm talking about Hotel Prison,
Teddy Bommer.

00:02:44.564 --> 00:02:47.333
I'd rather not, Spike Spiegel.

00:02:47.400 --> 00:02:49.335
Oh, you know me?

00:02:49.402 --> 00:02:51.905
It's a popular story among criminals

00:02:52.572 --> 00:02:55.241
that we never want to be caught
by you, or by Andy.

00:02:55.308 --> 00:02:56.175
Andy?

00:02:57.911 --> 00:02:59.779
I will fulfill my objective!

00:03:12.792 --> 00:03:13.893
It won't blow up.

00:03:14.561 --> 00:03:16.229
I took out the ignition pin.

00:03:28.875 --> 00:03:31.311
Three million woolongs,
graciously accepted.

00:03:31.711 --> 00:03:32.845
That's not the only bear.

00:03:36.749 --> 00:03:37.784
You'll die, too.

00:03:38.284 --> 00:03:39.652
I love them to death.

00:03:39.986 --> 00:03:41.888
Why do you want
to blow stuff up so much?

00:03:42.755 --> 00:03:45.858
You wanna know? I'm giving a warning.

00:03:47.827 --> 00:03:49.829
I am ringing a bell of warning!

00:03:49.896 --> 00:03:52.532
All right, be mindful of what I say!

00:04:01.241 --> 00:04:02.275
Andy.

00:04:11.718 --> 00:04:12.652
Andy?

00:04:16.923 --> 00:04:18.524
Call me Wyatt Earp.

00:04:19.659 --> 00:04:22.462
You! Teddy Bommer, serial bomber!

00:04:22.528 --> 00:04:23.396
Me?!

00:04:23.896 --> 00:04:26.032
The fact that you'd plant
a bomb here today

00:04:26.499 --> 00:04:30.803
was easy for me to figure out
after calculating your criminal cycles.

00:04:30.870 --> 00:04:32.505
You don't think it's him?

00:04:35.341 --> 00:04:36.709
He's a security guard!

00:04:36.776 --> 00:04:38.011
Just look at his face!

00:04:38.811 --> 00:04:41.514
In this day and age, a face means nothing.

00:04:41.581 --> 00:04:43.883
Then what is the basis of your theory?

00:04:43.950 --> 00:04:44.951
That is--

00:04:45.318 --> 00:04:47.854
My gut instinct. Yes, inspiration!

00:04:50.657 --> 00:04:51.624
Hey, wait!

00:04:51.691 --> 00:04:52.759
Wait!

00:05:06.706 --> 00:05:07.674
Oh, shit.

00:05:08.074 --> 00:05:11.411
That's why I said
Teddy Bommer was that guy, you idiot!

00:05:11.644 --> 00:05:12.645
Dangerous!

00:05:25.825 --> 00:05:27.093
That was a close one.

00:05:46.713 --> 00:05:48.614
-A horse?
-Yeah, a horse.

00:05:49.716 --> 00:05:50.616
A horse, huh?

00:05:51.084 --> 00:05:54.887
I thought it was fishy when you said
you'd nab that guy as part of your trip.

00:05:55.088 --> 00:05:56.422
What do you mean by that?

00:05:56.489 --> 00:05:58.725
You used the food money for all of us,
didn't you?

00:05:58.791 --> 00:06:00.426
-Come on.
-What did you use it on?

00:06:00.493 --> 00:06:03.429
If you think I'm lying,
explain this on my back!

00:06:03.496 --> 00:06:04.497
All right, I hear you.

00:06:05.031 --> 00:06:06.933
-The horse I can believe.
-You can?

00:06:06.999 --> 00:06:10.536
But you have to be more creative
than a cowboy in a cowboy outfit.

00:06:10.770 --> 00:06:12.004
Is that the problem?

00:06:12.572 --> 00:06:16.109
-Now, if he was dressed like a samurai...
-That would be more plausible.

00:06:19.512 --> 00:06:21.681
Here he is, little Andy!

00:06:22.448 --> 00:06:25.885
"Little Andy is a guy in the YMCA."

00:06:25.952 --> 00:06:26.886
A Christian?

00:06:26.953 --> 00:06:30.590
Nope. Young Men's Cowboy Association!

00:06:31.824 --> 00:06:32.925
Such a thing exists?

00:06:33.526 --> 00:06:35.528
But he got kicked out soon after joining.

00:06:35.828 --> 00:06:36.829
The reason?

00:06:36.896 --> 00:06:38.698
Because he caused others trouble!

00:06:38.765 --> 00:06:39.665
Of course!

00:06:39.899 --> 00:06:44.504
"Andy von de Oniyate,
the noble son of Oniyate Ranch."

00:06:44.804 --> 00:06:46.506
Hey, he's pretty cute.

00:06:46.572 --> 00:06:48.975
"A hundred and twenty-three cases
of property damage.

00:06:49.041 --> 00:06:51.911
Eighty-nine cases
of destruction of public property."

00:06:51.978 --> 00:06:53.479
Many, many people injured.

00:06:53.546 --> 00:06:55.047
A good match for someone we know.

00:06:55.114 --> 00:06:57.583
-I told you he existed!
-All right, I hear you.

00:07:05.958 --> 00:07:07.827
-Any reactions?
<i>-None yet.</i>

00:07:08.728 --> 00:07:09.595
However...

00:07:10.062 --> 00:07:13.166
we can't let it explode
with all these people around.

00:07:13.833 --> 00:07:15.568
<i>His only target is the building.</i>

00:07:15.935 --> 00:07:17.603
<i>He's not one for murder.</i>

00:07:17.804 --> 00:07:19.138
You think we can trust him?

00:07:19.539 --> 00:07:22.508
<i>Guys like him are often concerned</i>
<i>with their sense of style.</i>

00:07:23.776 --> 00:07:26.913
Well, this is the perfect party
to hide yourself.

00:07:31.751 --> 00:07:34.120
Did you know that a serial bomber
is gonna come here?

00:07:34.187 --> 00:07:35.922
To tell the truth, I didn't know.

00:07:38.624 --> 00:07:39.492
Well, he's coming.

00:07:41.127 --> 00:07:41.994
Hey!

00:07:43.896 --> 00:07:46.566
The world is about love and peace!

00:07:48.234 --> 00:07:51.103
-Yo.
-How did you know it was me?

00:07:51.170 --> 00:07:53.873
This lead the way to its papa.

00:07:54.507 --> 00:07:56.209
I think I would've known in either case.

00:07:56.843 --> 00:07:58.878
You guys just don't quit, do you?

00:07:58.945 --> 00:07:59.846
Speak for yourself.

00:07:59.912 --> 00:08:01.848
Why do you want
to blow things up so much?

00:08:02.715 --> 00:08:03.749
You wanna know?

00:08:03.816 --> 00:08:05.785
I am giving out a warning.

00:08:06.586 --> 00:08:09.255
Listen, in this world,
the root of all evil--

00:08:22.635 --> 00:08:23.769
A horse.

00:08:26.205 --> 00:08:27.707
A cowboy.

00:08:31.511 --> 00:08:34.280
-Hey, you! Teddy Bommer!
-Me?!

00:08:34.947 --> 00:08:37.116
-See, I told you.
-Or is it you over there?

00:08:37.683 --> 00:08:39.051
Do you have no memory?!

00:08:39.719 --> 00:08:41.020
We met just yesterday!

00:08:42.255 --> 00:08:43.556
I have no recollection.

00:08:43.623 --> 00:08:44.857
You!

00:08:44.924 --> 00:08:47.827
Sir, your horse is an inconvenience.

00:08:47.894 --> 00:08:50.229
It proves rather troublesome
for our other customers.

00:08:50.296 --> 00:08:53.165
Oh, my beloved steed, Onyx,
is no ordinary horse!

00:08:53.232 --> 00:08:55.234
At times,
she sets my troubled mind at ease,

00:08:55.301 --> 00:08:58.170
-at others she is my chess partner.
-Like horses play chess!

00:08:58.237 --> 00:08:59.939
It doesn't matter either way.

00:09:00.006 --> 00:09:02.742
I detest being ignored!

00:09:16.856 --> 00:09:18.791
What happened to his sense of style?!

00:09:18.858 --> 00:09:21.761
Calm down! I'm telling you to calm down!

00:09:22.628 --> 00:09:24.130
Love and peace, man!

00:09:31.571 --> 00:09:32.872
Such a lovely horse.

00:09:33.139 --> 00:09:34.640
Do you like her?

00:09:35.308 --> 00:09:37.109
Would you like to be my escort?

00:09:38.110 --> 00:09:39.245
Now, get behind me.

00:10:20.119 --> 00:10:20.987
You little--

00:11:12.271 --> 00:11:14.240
In my life, I've never seen such a...

00:11:15.007 --> 00:11:16.342
tasteless room.

00:11:19.211 --> 00:11:23.315
Now, I present you with my
special son-of-a-gun stew.

00:11:26.419 --> 00:11:28.854
I'm sure you'll find it
extremely delicious.

00:11:37.430 --> 00:11:40.199
So, why are you a bounty hunter?

00:11:40.466 --> 00:11:44.336
If you're so rich-- I mean,
if you have so much comfort in your life.

00:11:44.403 --> 00:11:47.106
Why? Let's see.

00:11:47.706 --> 00:11:50.309
Because it suits me.

00:11:52.211 --> 00:11:55.047
That feeling a cowboy gets
when he corners a bull.

00:11:59.251 --> 00:12:03.222
But you don't have to go after
such a dangerous bounty, do you?

00:12:04.090 --> 00:12:07.927
I know why nobody wants
to go after Teddy Bommer.

00:12:09.061 --> 00:12:12.331
Nobody wants
to get a piece of the explosion.

00:12:12.398 --> 00:12:14.066
You think we can worry about that?

00:12:14.133 --> 00:12:17.203
Yes! I don't worry about things like that!

00:12:17.436 --> 00:12:20.873
Once I set my mind on something,
I can see nothing else!

00:12:23.943 --> 00:12:26.245
I think I've seen this personality
somewhere before.

00:12:27.947 --> 00:12:28.981
Oh, nothing.

00:12:29.915 --> 00:12:30.816
Now!

00:12:31.851 --> 00:12:33.185
Here's looking at...

00:12:33.953 --> 00:12:35.754
my reflection, kid.

00:12:37.423 --> 00:12:38.324
Cheers.

00:12:47.333 --> 00:12:48.434
Hi, I got a souvenir.

00:12:52.471 --> 00:12:54.940
A souvenir! A souvenir!

00:12:55.274 --> 00:12:57.243
I ain't gonna eat that!

00:12:58.077 --> 00:12:59.345
Guess this is for dinner.

00:12:59.545 --> 00:13:00.779
I will not eat that.

00:13:04.183 --> 00:13:05.317
Your stomach will suffer.

00:13:06.252 --> 00:13:10.489
But what about him makes you so hotheaded?

00:13:11.090 --> 00:13:12.191
They're too similar.

00:13:12.992 --> 00:13:14.994
You know how
similar people hate each other.

00:13:15.528 --> 00:13:18.164
What part of me is similar
to that shit-headed idiot?!

00:13:18.831 --> 00:13:20.566
The part that makes you damn troublesome.

00:13:23.869 --> 00:13:26.038
Oh, big shot has already started.

00:13:27.006 --> 00:13:31.110
{\an8}<i>Well, the last thing we have to tell you</i>
<i>is info about T.B., Teddy Bommer.</i>

00:13:31.177 --> 00:13:32.144
<i>Can you believe it?</i>

00:13:32.211 --> 00:13:34.580
<i>We got a message from him,</i>
<i>just for this show!</i>

00:13:34.847 --> 00:13:36.482
<i>What? Is that for real?</i>

00:13:37.416 --> 00:13:38.384
<i>Let's see.</i>

00:13:39.051 --> 00:13:43.122
<i>"Warning: This is for those</i>
<i>that have made fun of me.</i>

00:13:43.522 --> 00:13:45.558
<i>My next job is your last chance.</i>

00:13:45.824 --> 00:13:49.195
<i>This time, I'll blow you up as well,</i>
<i>like fireworks."</i>

00:13:49.862 --> 00:13:51.397
<i>My, my, he doesn't sound calm.</i>

00:13:51.597 --> 00:13:54.867
<i>"That is,</i>
<i>if you know where I will set up next.</i>

00:13:55.834 --> 00:13:59.104
<i>And lastly,</i>
<i>I will tell you my true intent--"</i>

00:13:59.171 --> 00:14:03.475
<i>Whoops, looks like time is up for us.</i>
<i>That's all for today.</i>

00:14:03.976 --> 00:14:06.045
<i>I'm sorry I couldn't read all of it, T.B.</i>

00:14:06.111 --> 00:14:07.947
<i>Well, until next time.</i>

00:14:08.013 --> 00:14:09.081
<i>Good luck!</i>

00:14:15.321 --> 00:14:16.989
The next one's in city hall.

00:14:17.056 --> 00:14:18.257
You figured it out already?

00:14:18.324 --> 00:14:21.594
T.B. is blowing up tall buildings
starting with the tallest one.

00:14:22.228 --> 00:14:24.029
The reason was that simple?

00:14:24.430 --> 00:14:26.899
What are you gonna do?
I'm getting out of this one.

00:14:27.499 --> 00:14:29.034
I'm gonna pass, too.

00:14:29.435 --> 00:14:31.070
Spike, what are you going to do?

00:14:32.338 --> 00:14:33.472
<i>Like you have to ask?!</i>

00:14:40.246 --> 00:14:41.280
Late!

00:14:41.947 --> 00:14:45.885
Damn it! If they think they can get away
with this, they are sorely mistaken!

00:14:49.321 --> 00:14:52.358
-You alone?
-How dare you take so long to get here?

00:14:52.424 --> 00:14:53.459
Wait!

00:14:56.061 --> 00:14:56.996
Wrong guy.

00:14:58.497 --> 00:15:01.433
I never intended for humans to be targets!

00:15:01.500 --> 00:15:03.535
But you guys are different!

00:15:04.203 --> 00:15:06.105
Guys like you deserve--

00:15:16.548 --> 00:15:17.416
He's here.

00:15:21.453 --> 00:15:23.022
You! It was you!

00:15:23.322 --> 00:15:24.556
So, you finally remember me.

00:15:25.291 --> 00:15:29.228
-You always--
-You always butt in and get in my way!

00:15:30.562 --> 00:15:32.197
You're the one that's in the way!

00:15:32.998 --> 00:15:35.234
Now that I have both of you here,
I will tell you.

00:15:35.301 --> 00:15:38.370
The reason why I continue
to blow buildings up is because--

00:15:39.038 --> 00:15:41.006
Today we settle the score
once and for all.

00:15:41.073 --> 00:15:43.008
What?! That's my line!

00:15:43.075 --> 00:15:44.576
Listen to what I have to say!

00:15:44.643 --> 00:15:46.011
-Shut up!
-Shut up!

00:15:46.078 --> 00:15:47.947
And you are? Who are you?!

00:15:52.084 --> 00:15:54.219
Can't you guys put some effort
into your work?!

00:15:59.191 --> 00:16:01.193
-We have to catch him first!
-Wait!

00:16:13.038 --> 00:16:15.341
<i>You guys take me too lightly.</i>

00:16:16.008 --> 00:16:19.078
<i>That elevator door will never open again.</i>

00:16:19.311 --> 00:16:22.314
<i>And once it starts moving, that's the end.</i>
<i>It will never stop.</i>

00:16:22.381 --> 00:16:28.454
At the top floor,
my cute little bears will greet you.

00:16:28.520 --> 00:16:31.423
So, the moment that the elevator
reaches the top floor...

00:16:32.091 --> 00:16:33.058
boom!

00:16:36.729 --> 00:16:41.400
<i>Well, live what little you have</i>
<i>of your life left without regret!</i>

00:16:43.268 --> 00:16:44.570
<i>Farewell, and good luck.</i>

00:16:51.410 --> 00:16:54.513
Rest assured. I understand.
I know how he does things.

00:16:55.180 --> 00:16:58.550
Don't worry. I know how he does--

00:16:59.651 --> 00:17:02.154
This afternoon,
I reverted the secret emergency code

00:17:02.221 --> 00:17:05.190
that had been changed. Yeah.

00:17:05.257 --> 00:17:07.493
I reverted it this afternoon!

00:17:10.329 --> 00:17:12.398
Change after change...

00:17:13.032 --> 00:17:15.334
means it's back to where it started!

00:17:18.570 --> 00:17:19.605
Stop, you idiot!

00:17:19.671 --> 00:17:22.775
What do we do?! What do we do?! Oh, no!

00:17:35.254 --> 00:17:37.489
Stop. Shit. It's too tight!

00:17:37.556 --> 00:17:40.325
-You are in the way!
-What? Get out of the way, damn it!

00:18:05.851 --> 00:18:07.119
Farewell.

00:18:07.719 --> 00:18:10.589
Come to think of it,
they were brave young men.

00:18:40.319 --> 00:18:42.688
They're climbing, those two monkeys.

00:18:43.388 --> 00:18:45.257
They like high places.

00:18:45.557 --> 00:18:47.159
So, they are similar.

00:18:47.793 --> 00:18:48.827
Let's just go back.

00:18:49.394 --> 00:18:52.331
Then I'll go turn him in.

00:19:01.373 --> 00:19:04.243
You don't even deserve
to be called a cowboy.

00:19:05.477 --> 00:19:07.479
I will never forgive you.

00:20:28.527 --> 00:20:29.494
I lose.

00:20:30.495 --> 00:20:31.530
That was some punch.

00:20:34.466 --> 00:20:36.368
You are a true cowboy.

00:20:41.006 --> 00:20:43.408
As of today, I will no longer be a cowboy.

00:20:44.343 --> 00:20:46.278
This really is a hats-off!

00:20:49.248 --> 00:20:51.283
So... what are you gonna do now?

00:20:52.784 --> 00:20:55.520
I will no doubt find a new way of life.

00:20:57.689 --> 00:20:59.491
See you, Space Cowboy.

00:21:11.937 --> 00:21:14.473
Well, it was only a rich boy's hobby.

00:21:14.873 --> 00:21:18.377
His level, no, rank,
was really no match for me.

00:21:18.877 --> 00:21:20.579
Hey, are you listening?

00:21:20.646 --> 00:21:21.580
Yeah, yeah.

00:21:21.880 --> 00:21:24.616
So, he just wasn't any enemy of mine.

00:21:24.683 --> 00:21:27.319
Of course,
I never had him in my line of sight.

00:21:31.556 --> 00:21:33.292
-Hey, are you listening?
-Yeah, yeah.

00:21:35.827 --> 00:21:39.931
But, anyway, why did you want
to blow stuff up so much?

00:21:41.733 --> 00:21:43.835
I wanted to give a warning...

00:21:45.304 --> 00:21:49.041
about all the unnecessary waste
created by capitalism lacking philosophy.

00:21:50.409 --> 00:21:52.077
Planets that needlessly gets colonized.

00:21:52.744 --> 00:21:54.579
Media that needlessly gets circulated.

00:21:54.646 --> 00:21:57.449
And buildings that are needlessly tall
to symbolize it all!

00:21:57.983 --> 00:21:59.918
And by destroying them, I wanted to raise

00:22:00.552 --> 00:22:03.822
the question
of how a true pioneer should be.

00:22:03.889 --> 00:22:05.424
Wait, wait, wait!

00:22:08.060 --> 00:22:08.994
Andy!

00:22:09.661 --> 00:22:10.996
Call me Musashi!

00:22:12.030 --> 00:22:14.566
Go, Jiroumaru!

00:22:16.702 --> 00:22:17.703
But...

00:22:18.704 --> 00:22:20.772
it was all a waste, wasn't it?

00:22:45.597 --> 00:22:50.702
<i>Too much time has passed by</i>

00:22:51.603 --> 00:22:55.841
<i>To lament that we were deeply in love</i>

00:22:57.576 --> 00:23:02.614
<i>The wind keeps blowing, while my heart</i>

00:23:03.615 --> 00:23:07.853
<i>Cannot heal all the tears in it</i>

00:23:09.921 --> 00:23:16.928
<i>Someone cry for me with parched eyes.</i>

00:23:20.632 --> 00:23:23.802
<i>The real folk blues</i>

00:23:24.002 --> 00:23:26.671
<i>I only want to know</i>

00:23:28.173 --> 00:23:32.177
<i>What true sadness is</i>

00:23:32.611 --> 00:23:35.447
<i>Sitting in muddy water</i>

00:23:36.047 --> 00:23:38.784
<i>Isn't such a bad life</i>

00:23:40.152 --> 00:23:47.159
<i>If it ends</i>

00:23:49.961 --> 00:23:52.998
<i>After the first time</i>

00:24:11.917 --> 00:24:14.619
<i>Did you pay close attention to me</i>
<i>and my wonderful role?</i>

00:24:14.686 --> 00:24:15.854
<i>Hey, wait a minute.</i>

00:24:15.921 --> 00:24:19.191
<i>-Now, the next episode, the next story--</i>
<i>-Why are you doing the preview?</i>

00:24:19.457 --> 00:24:22.460
<i>Once again, it's time for me, Andy,</i>
<i>to have an active role in the story!</i>

00:24:22.527 --> 00:24:24.196
<i>Your turn on the stage is already over!</i>

00:24:24.462 --> 00:24:25.730
<i>Now that I'm a space samurai,</i>

